race.comment: DRAGON TALES (1) missed a whisker heavily bet at Townsville before the spell and resumed there and found one too good. Fitter and the longer sprint shouldn't be an issue. He will take plenty of beating.  FILLYDELPHIA MISS (5) was plainer at Bowen but her near miss at Townsville two back would have her right in this. Has been kept on the fresh side and is likely to push forward. Has claims at odds. VAN DER WOODSEN (7) is a former Victorian better for the first-up run for the new yard. Quick improvement is on the cards, PROMPTLY (2) debuts and has been switched from a high-striking Scone yard. Has Cartwright aboard and a low barrier and keep a close eye on the betting.
